USA Overall

As of yesterday, there has been a total of 29,188,304 cases of COVID-19 in the USA. This is a change of 55,631 (0.19%) new cases since the day prior. The 7 day moving average is currently 6.447e+04 new cases which is a -4.37% change since the day prior and 3.92% change since the week prior. The immediate trend is heading upward. Based on the addition of yesterdays data, yesterday was not an inflection point (days since last inflection point: 2 > 2021-03-08).

7-day moving average of new cases in the US (2020-01-21 to 2021-03-09)

References

ICU stress definitions:

  • low: less than 10% of ICU Usage
  • moderate: 10-29% of ICU Usage
  • high: 30-59% of ICU Usage
  • extreme: greater than 60% of ICU Usage

Inpatient stress definitions:

  • low: less than 5% of hospital beds occupied by COVID-19 patients
  • moderate: 5-9% of hospital beds occupied by COVID-19 patients
  • high: 10-19% of hospital beds occupied by COVID-19 patients
  • extreme: greater than 20% of hospital beds occupied by COVID-19 patients
